channel.title: Back for brain stimulation
channel.description:
First of all: Holy shit, how's it going everyone? It's been a hell of a long time since I have last been [i]truly[/i] active on this forum, but hey, we all progress. But now I am back for who knows how long, for the purpose of [i]kick-ass[/i] brain stimulation, or in other words, programming re-education and practice. Client hacking is where I started, then SCAR came along and I had some fun times experimenting with scripts, and eventually I moved on to Java bot scripting and modifying. Java has been my overall favorite programming language, but it has been too long since I've last messed around with it. Last year I messed around with making some scripts for RSbot, but really did nothing with what I made (was just for shits 'n' giggles) and haven't done anything Java applet related since. Now, I need to get the ball rolling again but this time mainly for web development. My plans are revolving around eCommerce web design, so I can get the ball rolling with a career and some cash$$$. So now I've been focused on PHP/MySQL so I can get a proper website built, and of course I've been practicing all of this on a local Apache server (I must admit, I cheated and used XAMPP this time on my laptop, but hey, I've proved to myself I can do it without that on Knoppix).
Anyways, I just felt like a proper re-introduction of myself was necessary, at least, just to prove I have some manners. :P
I might browse around on the SCAR forums a bit just to have some fun and have a few memory flashbacks.
So now you know why I came back here, and if you still don't get it, here: Mopar IS the BEST. Best place to get acquainted with simple Java programming. Best place to kick back and discuss program languages in general. That is my opinion at least.
Cheers, ~Dizzy :cool:
